main event: An observation of a shiny object similar to a meteor was reported on 2 Jan 69.
interesting points: The object was observed for a duration of 45 minutes.,The object flew from west to east along the horizon.,The altitude of the object was noted as quite brilliant with a possible clear trail of illumination.,The report indicates it may have been a meteor.,The observation was part of an emergency report distributed to multiple military and government agencies.
witness description: Not specified, observed from a position with coordinates 35-06N 129-57W.
